{%- doc -%}
  Shared atmosphere primitive — a small cluster of extremely faint
  floating light particles, used by dark sections to feel like there's
  ambient energy in the background rather than a flat color. See
  dce-layout.css for the shared .dce-particles class/keyframe (kept
  there, not per-component, so every section reuses the same rule
  instead of redeclaring it — see docs/00-principles.md).

  Purely decorative (aria-hidden) and gated by data-dce-animate="glow"
  so it fades in only once the section actually scrolls into view,
  instead of just sitting there from page load.

  @param {number} [count] - How many particles (default 3). Keep this
    low — it should read as "faint atmosphere," never as a starfield.
    Hero is the one exception (5), because it's the one moment on the
    page meant to feel most alive.

  @example
  {% render 'dce-particles', count: 3 %}
{%- enddoc -%}

{%- liquid
  assign dce_particle_count = count | default: 3
-%}
<div class="dce-particles" data-dce-animate="glow" aria-hidden="true">
  {%- for i in (1..dce_particle_count) -%}
    <span></span>
  {%- endfor -%}
</div>
